headlines.description: Teddy Allen scored 22 points, Lamont West added 19 and sixth-ranked West Virginia beat pesky Kansas State 77-69 on Monday to push the Mountaineers' winning streak to 13 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 6 West Virginia holds off Kansas State, 77-69

video.headline: West Virginia pulls away from Kansas State

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Highlight (West Virginia pulls away from Kansas State) 2018/01/01 ESHEET

headlines.description: Abdulai Bundu blocked Ahsante Shivers' shot at the rim to preserve Quinnipiac's 71-70 victory over Siena on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bundu's block saves Quinnipiac's 71-70 win over Siena

headlines.description: B.J. Glasford scored all 16 of his points and Angel Rivera all but one of his 15 in the second half to help rally Stetson to a 94-88 victory over Florida National on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stetson comes back from 18-point deficit to win 94-88

headlines.description: Cameron Morse answered Bobby Word's 3-pointer with a long, contested one of his own with 0.6 seconds remaining, giving Youngstown State its first Division-I victory of the season, 80-77 over Cleveland State in a Horizon League opener on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morse's 3-pointer with 0.6 left gives Penguins 80-77 victory

headlines.description: De'Ederick Petty scored 18 points and Alabama A&M beat Grambling 71-64 on Monday for the Bulldogs' first victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alabama A&M beats Grambling 71-64 for first win of season

headlines.description: Martaveous McKnight scored 23 points and Arkansas-Pine Bluff beat Mississippi Valley State 80-71 on Monday night for its first victory of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas-Pine Bluff wins 1st game of season, 80-71 over MVSU

headlines.description: Dennis Jones had 15 points and 10 assists, Gary Blackston added 13 points and six assists, and Prairie View A&M beat Alcorn State 76-64 on Monday night in a Southwestern Athletic Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Prairie View A&M beats Alcorn State 76-64 in SWAC opener

headlines.description: Dylan Osetkowski scored a career-high 25 points with seven 3-pointers -- including the go-ahead bucket with 33.5 seconds left in overtime -- and Texas beat Iowa State 74-70 on Monday night to improve to 3-0 on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas upends Iowa State 74-70 in OT

headlines.description: Jeremiah Jefferson scored 21 points, Paris Collins had 16 points, 12 rebounds and five assists for his second double-double of the season, and Jackson State beat Alabama State 82-73 on Monday night in a Southwestern Athletic Conference opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson State beats Alabama State 82-73 in SWAC opener

venue.fullName: Lee E. Williams Athletic and Assembly Center

headlines.description: Derrick Bruce scored a career-high 28 points, Demontrae Jefferson added 25 and the duo combined for 13 3-pointers in Texas Southern's 78-66 victory over Southern on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas Southern hits 15 3s, beats Southern 78-66 for 1st win

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
